def solve():
    n = int(input())
    a = [int(i) for i in input().split()]
    q = set()
    for i in a:
        while i % 10 != 0 and i % 10 != 2:
            i += i % 10
        if i % 10 != 0:
            i %= 20
        q.add(i)
    return 'Yes' if len(q) == 1 else 'No'
t = int(input())
q = []
while t:
    q.append(solve())
    t -= 1
print('\n'.join(q))
